1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:04,440
A top figure in Huawei was arrested in Canada.

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:06,180
Now the Chinese government is threatening:

3
00:00:06,180 --> 00:00:08,570
“Release her, or else.”

4
00:00:08,570 --> 00:00:12,160
And Canada says, “Or else, what...eh?”

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:17,400
Welcome back to China Uncensored.

6
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,680
I’m Chris Chappell.

7
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,340
This is Meng Wanzhou.

8
00:00:20,350 --> 00:00:22,580
She’s the Chief Financial Officer

9
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:25,340
of China’s biggest private company, Huawei.

10
00:00:25,340 --> 00:00:27,900
But she made a big mistake:

11
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,140
Going to Canada.

12
00:00:29,140 --> 00:00:32,800
See, Meng was at the Vancouver airport on
December 1st,

13
00:00:32,809 --> 00:00:35,980
changing flights, when Canadian authorities
arrested her.

14
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:39,430
She’s suspected of orchestrating a scheme
by Huawei

15
00:00:39,430 --> 00:00:41,350
to use the global banking system

16
00:00:41,350 --> 00:00:44,350
to evade U.S. sanctions on Iran.

17
00:00:44,350 --> 00:00:47,440
And now she’s stuck in a Vancouver-area
prison

18
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:50,430
called the Alouette Correctional Facility
Center for Women.

19
00:00:50,430 --> 00:00:53,050
The Alouette is a dangerous place.

20
00:00:53,050 --> 00:00:56,020
First they pluck the feathers off your head,

21
00:00:56,020 --> 00:00:59,460
then your beak, then your neck...

22
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:01,379
And that was a very obscure joke

23
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:04,460
for all 3 of you who speak French.

24
00:01:04,460 --> 00:01:07,930
Anyway, Meng’s arrest in Canada ought to
be a lesson:

25
00:01:07,930 --> 00:01:09,220
She should have spent her winter visiting

26
00:01:09,220 --> 00:01:12,270
a tropical island nation like Vanuatu.

27
00:01:12,270 --> 00:01:13,630
Not so much for the warm weather—

28
00:01:13,630 --> 00:01:17,100
but because they don’t have an extradition
treaty with the US.

29
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:21,560
Meng was arrested in Canada at the request
of US authorities.

30
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:24,359
The US accuses her of misleading multinational
banks

31
00:01:24,359 --> 00:01:28,679
about Huawei’s control of a company operating
in Iran,

32
00:01:28,679 --> 00:01:31,819
putting the banks at risk of violating US
sanctions

33
00:01:31,819 --> 00:01:35,029
and potentially incurring severe penalties.

34
00:01:35,029 --> 00:01:37,789
If extradited to the US and convicted here,

35
00:01:37,789 --> 00:01:40,649
she could face up to 30 years in prison.

36
00:01:40,649 --> 00:01:43,450
But even in her temporary Canadian jail,

37
00:01:43,450 --> 00:01:45,540
she’s been badly abused.

38
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,680
Don't take it from me.

39
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:50,829
Take it from my favorite Chinese state-run
media The Global Times.

40
00:01:50,829 --> 00:01:53,749
They say her human rights are being violated.

41
00:01:53,749 --> 00:01:54,749
They write that,

42
00:01:54,749 --> 00:01:58,180
“She has been subjected to rude and degrading
treatment.”

43
00:01:58,180 --> 00:01:58,980
For example,

44
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:02,080
being put in handcuffs and even ankle braces.

45
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,130
I agree.

46
00:02:03,130 --> 00:02:06,609
How dare Canada treat her like a common Chinese
dissident!

47
00:02:06,609 --> 00:02:09,440
She’s a VIP with connections!

48
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,840
Actually, that’s not true.

49
00:02:10,849 --> 00:02:13,019
A common Chinese dissident would have been
beaten up

50
