on behalf of the Chinese Communist Party,

61
00:02:45,769 --> 00:02:47,500
and of undermining American security

62
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:51,049
by illegally using advanced US technology

63
00:02:51,049 --> 00:02:53,799
to give the Chinese military an edge.

64
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:55,250
Richard Fisher, Senior Fellow

65
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:58,060
at the International Assessment and Strategy
Center,

66
00:02:58,060 --> 00:02:59,849
told The Epoch Times that Huawei

67
00:02:59,849 --> 00:03:03,129
and another Chinese company ZTE are quote
unquote

68
00:03:03,129 --> 00:03:07,049
“cat’s paws for Chinese Communist Party
domination.”

69
00:03:07,049 --> 00:03:09,049
Now that should really give you pause.

70
00:03:09,049 --> 00:03:14,110
The Chinese company ZTE is a competitor of
Huawei.

71
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,829
And the US recently banned ZTE

72
00:03:15,829 --> 00:03:18,890
from buying components from U.S. manufacturers.

73
00:03:18,890 --> 00:03:21,790
It was punishment for illegally selling telecom
equipment

74
00:03:21,790 --> 00:03:26,129
containing American technology to Iran and
North Korea.

75
00:03:26,129 --> 00:03:28,799
And Huawei could soon face similar sanctions.

76
00:03:28,799 --> 00:03:30,819
Because it’s also under investigation

77
00:03:30,819 --> 00:03:32,780
by the US Department of Justice

78
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:35,040
for violating Iran sanctions.

79
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:37,359
So it’s little wonder that the Chinese Communist
Party

80
00:03:37,359 --> 00:03:41,409
has rushed to threaten Canada over Meng Wanzhou’s
arrest.

81
00:03:41,409 --> 00:03:44,349
Here’s my favorite Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesperson

82
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,800
and second-favorite Mortal Kombat character,

83
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,600
