125
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:36,270
This is something maybe Chinese authorities
don’t understand.

126
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:38,620
But Canada—yes, Canada—

127
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:40,410
does have rule of law.

128
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:43,370
“The Prime Minister or Minister cannot phone
the judge

129
00:05:43,370 --> 00:05:45,580
and tell them to release the person,

130
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:48,430
so what’s China demanding under our rule
of law,

131
00:05:48,430 --> 00:05:49,960
under our system,

132
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:51,860
is not a doable thing.

133
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,860
That being said,

134
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:54,509
China certainly has the means

135
00:05:54,509 --> 00:05:58,069
to inflict pain on its relationship with Canada.”

136
00:05:58,069 --> 00:06:00,940
So after all of the Chinese regime’s confusing
threats

137
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:03,190
that didn’t sound like threats,

138
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:07,629
it finally took Party mouthpiece People’s
Daily to lay it on straight.

139
00:06:07,629 --> 00:06:09,909
They directly warned Canada that

140
00:06:09,909 --> 00:06:13,509
“The only way to avoid paying a much heavier
price

141
00:06:13,509 --> 00:06:17,240
is for the Canadian side to correct this error.”

142
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,770
So what they’re saying is...

143
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:22,470
Unless Canadian politicians break the law,

144
00:06:22,470 --> 00:06:24,710
violate their extradition treaty with the
US,

145
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:26,160
and release Meng,

146
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,539
there’ll be hell to pay.

147
00:06:28,539 --> 00:06:31,710
So how did Shiny Pony react to that?

148
00:06:31,710 --> 00:06:35,090
“As I said the appropriate authorities

149
